            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Nutrition </u></b> <br>
                Provide a balanced diet appropriate for your dog's age, size, and breed. Choose high-quality dog food 
                and ensure access to fresh water at all times.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Exercise </u> </b> <br>
                Keep your dog active with daily walks, playtime, or trips to the dog park. Regular exercise is vital 
                for their physical and mental well-being.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Grooming </u></b> <br>
                Regular brushing, occasional baths, nail trimming, and ear cleaning are essential for your dog's 
                hygiene and appearance.
            </p>  
            <p>
                <b> <u> Healthcare </u></b> <br>
                Schedule regular check-ups with your veterinarian for vaccinations, parasite control, and 
                dental care to ensure your dog stays healthy.
            </p>   
            <p>
                <b> <u> Training </u> </b> <br>
                Basic obedience training helps establish boundaries and strengthens the bond between you 
                and your dog. Use positive reinforcement techniques for best results.
            </p>   
            <p>
                <b> <u> Conclusion </u> </b> <br>
                By following these simple tips for dog care, you can ensure that your furry friend enjoys 
                a happy and healthy life by your side.
